title: Ultimate Minecraft Quiz (HARD)
briefDescription: 35 questions, 4 choices each. Test how much do you know about the game while playing it!The quiz covers a large amount of Minecraft game modes ...

crawledImageUrls.text:
35 questions, 4 choices each. Test how much do you know about the game while playing it!
The quiz covers a large amount of Minecraft game modes and types. It also features several odd one out questions which makes the quiz even more challenging.
This test is split into 2 distinct sections:
Section 1, basic questions. 30 questions are in this section. Answer correctly to get 1 emerald, which represents your total score. No mark penalty is imposed for wrong answers. Every 5 questions you will have to teleport to another subsection to continue. I hint what version of Minecraft is being referred to in the questions. The picture below shows the outside of section 1.

Section 2, advanced questions (even though the test is generally hard). 5 questions are in the section. Answer correctly to get 2 emeralds, but a wrong answer will cost you one. These questions are skippable (use the green button on the ceiling) and skipping imposes no mark penalty. This is meant to deter people from guessing answers to get a pass.
At the end room, use the number of emeralds (1 emerald = 1 mark) to know how many marks out of 40 you get, and different score ranges have different feedback.
Screenshots of the map:
Here is a photo of one of the questions.
Another question:
At the end room, you can find a question 36 which says what I think about the predicted types of people after completing the map.
